<br><br>
<h2>The weather in January 2019</h2>
<br><br>
The main part of Western Europe was dominated by high pressure areas in January. Average temperatures were therefore above the 1981-2010 average in large parts of the United Kingdom, western Scandinavia and SW-Europe. Eastern and northeastern parts of Europe have seen much more changeable conditions with cold air outbreaks. The northern part of Scandinavia and the Alps had below average minimum temperatures (Figure 7). Many parts of Spain experienced a lot of days with far above normal maximum temperatures.
<br><br>
